WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:07.300
Kebab Hindi

00:00:07.300 --> 00:00:09.000
Serve: 6

00:00:09.000 --> 00:00:10.300
Ingredients :

00:00:10.300 --> 00:00:14.400
500 g ground lamb (10% fat)

00:00:14.400 --> 00:00:17.000
2 tbsp pine nuts, toasted

00:00:17.000 --> 00:00:20.500
1½  kg tomatoes, peeled and finely chopped

00:00:20.500 --> 00:00:22.700
2 onions, sliced

00:00:22.700 --> 00:00:25.800
6 garlic cloves, thinly sliced

00:00:25.800 --> 00:00:29.000
1 green bell pepper, seeded and sliced

00:00:29.000 --> 00:00:32.300
1 red bell pepper, seeded and sliced

00:00:32.300 --> 00:00:35.000
½ tsp ginger

00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:37.300
½ tsp ground cardamom

00:00:37.300 --> 00:00:39.600
½ tsp black pepper

00:00:39.600 --> 00:00:41.000
A pinch cinnamon

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:43.200
1 tsp tomato paste 

00:00:43.200 --> 00:00:47.800
1 tsp hot red pepper paste 

00:00:47.800 --> 00:00:49.300
Salt to taste

00:00:49.300 --> 00:00:51.500
2 tbsp vegetable oil

00:00:51.500 --> 00:00:53.000
Directions :

00:00:53.000 --> 00:01:00.500
Heat the oil in a large saucepan and sauté onion and garlic until soft and translucent

00:01:00.500 --> 00:01:05.500
then add the tomatoes and cook 30 minutes over low heat.

00:01:05.500 --> 00:01:16.500
In a bowl, mix the meat with 1 tbsp of pine nuts, add ½ tsp of salt and ¼ tsp of black pepper

00:01:16.500 --> 00:01:24.300
and shape the meat into little fingers.

00:01:24.300 --> 00:01:37.700
Add the spices to the tomatoes and add the salt, the red pepper paste and the tomato paste

00:01:37.700 --> 00:01:45.500
then add the red and green peppers and cook for 15 minutes then remove from heat. 

00:01:45.500 --> 00:01:59.000
Transfer over a baking tray and place the meat fingers and bake for 30 minutes in a preheated oven at 180°C. 

00:01:59.000 --> 00:02:04.000
After 20 minutes turn the meat.

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:10.000
Sprinkle the remaining pine nuts and serve with rice.

